## Introduction:
Tic Tac Toe is a classic game played on a 3x3 grid where players take turns marking spaces with their symbols (usually "X" and "O") until one player wins by placing three of their symbols in a row, column, or diagonal, or the game ends in a draw.

## FEATURES
-Play against a friend or against the computer AI.
-Simple and intuitive user interface.
-Automatic detection of the winner or draw.
-Replay option to start a new game.
-How to Play
  Open the game in a web browser.
  Select whether you want to play as "X" or "O".
<img src="public/img/tictactoe1.png" alt="Select">


  Click on the empty cells in the grid to make your move.
<img src="public/img/tictactoe2.png" alt="Select">

  If playing against the computer, wait for the AI to make its move.
  The game will automatically detect if there's a winner or if it's a draw.
  Use the replay button to start a new game.
<img src="public/img/tictactoe3.png" alt="Select">


## TECHNOLOGIES USED:
HTML
CSS
JavaScript
Usage
Clone the repository or download the files.
Open index.html in a web browser.
Follow the on-screen instructions to play the game.

